SYLVESTER, et al., Respondents, v. JACOBY, Appellant. (Common Pleas of New York City and County, General Term. March 8, 1894.) Appeal from special term. Action by Lewis Sylvester and another against Solomon M. Jacoby.

Argued before DALY, C. J., and PRYOR and GIEGERICH, JJ.

Wm. Armstrong, for appellant. Nichols & Baear, for respondents.

No opinion. Appeal dismissed for nonservice of printed papers, with $10 cost and disbursement, to abide the event of the action.
